    <note>Gao(1) Shenzhao [11695] He was orphaned at the age of three and was adopted by his maternal uncle, Wang(2) Quanbin [11689]. He had military talent and, upon the recommendation of Quanbin, was appointed to a military post and changed his surname back to Gao. He led the advance party in the attack on Northern Han for Taizong and was promoted after Hedong was pacified. His father-in-law, Ma(2) Wan (not in dataset), was a Fufeng Ma(2) and military officer. Song Qi, WJ, 59.20b-22a. CBD, 3, 1764.</note>
